product_name: Grande CosmeticsTravel Size GrandeLASH-MD Lash Enhancing Serum
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeGrandeLASH-MD Lash Enhancing Serum is an iconic serum proven to promote the appearance of longer thicker healthier looking lashes. From Grande Cosmetics, #1 Lash & Brow Serum Brand in the US*. Powered by a proprietary lash complex this serum creates luxury-level lashes.
details: DetailsBenefitsOnce daily, one swipe wonder!Paraben-freeSuitable for use with contact lenses, lash extensions, & false lashesKey IngredientsIsopropyl Cloprostenate: A prostaglandin analogue that helps to enhance the appearance of eyelashesRadish Root Ferment: Peptide-packed to conditionHoney & Aloe Vera: Soothe lashes & skinFeaturesGrandeLASH-MD has been tested for safety & performance in 10 third-party studies.In a 12-week consumer study using GrandeLASH-MD**:94% saw healthier looking lashes91% saw longer looking lashes97% saw more visible lashes**Based on a 12-week consumer study with 30 subjects. Results will vary.*Source: Circana/U.S. Prestige Beauty Total Measured Market, Lash/Brow Treatment Dollar Sales, Skincare Form/Texture: Serum, January ‚Äì April 2023 combinedItem 2561653How To UseAs with all cosmetic products used in the area of the eye (or close proximity to the eye), it is important to carefully read all directions and warnings. Carefully apply GrandeLASHMD once daily on a clean, dry upper lash line only using a single stroke on your eyelid just above your upper lash line (like a liquid eyeliner). Do not apply to the lower lash line. Apply only with the product applicator provided. Use one dip into the bottle for both upper lash lines and allow 2-3 minutes for the serum to fully dry before lying down or applying other products to your eye area. Use sparingly. If serum gets into the eye, immediately rinse thoroughly with cool water to completely remove serum from the eye. Apply every day for a full 3 months. After desired improvement is achieved, apply every other day for maintenance. GrandeLASH-MD requires continued use to maintain benefits.This cosmetic product contains (a small amount of) isopropyl cloprostenate, an analog of prostaglandin. It is important to use the product as instructed so that it does not get into the eye. As instructed in the directions for application, if product does come into contact with the eye, immediately rinse thoroughly with cool water to completely remove the cosmetic serum from the eye. If redness, irritation or other unwanted effects occur, stop using product immediately. If symptoms persist, seek medical attention.For external use. Avoid getting in eyes; if so, immediately rinse thoroughly with cool water. Not for use by customers under the age of 18. Do not use on damaged or irritated skin, if pregnant or nursing or undergoing treatment for glaucoma or cancer. Not recommended if you have ever experienced dry eyes, eye infections, styes or any other eye-related disorder. If redness, irritation or other unwanted effects occur, stop using product immediately. If symptoms persist, seek medical attention. Keep out of reach of children.IngredientsWater/Aqua/Eau, Panthenol, Glycerin, Sodium Citrate, Leuconostoc/Radish Root Ferment Filtrate, Alanine, Alcohol, Aloe Barbadensis Leaf Juice, Arctostaphylos Uva URSI Leaf Extract, Arginine, Aspartic Acid, Calcium Gluconate, Caprylyl Glycol, Chamomilla Recutita (Metricaria) Flower Extract, Ethylhexylglycerin, Gluconolactone, Glycine, Hexylene Glycol, Histidine, Honey Extract/Mel/Extrait de Miel, Hydrolyzed Glycosaminoglycans, Hydrolyzed Yeast Extract, Hydroxyethylcellulose, Isoleucine, Isopropyl Cloprostenate (an analog of prostaglandin), Magnesium Ascorbyl Phosphate, Panax Ginseng Root Extract, PCA, Phenylalanine, Polysorbate 20, Proline, Propylene Glycol, Serine, Sodium Hyaluronate, Sodium Lactate, Sodium PCA, Threonine, Tocopheryl Acetate, Triethanolamine, Tussilago Farfara (Coltsfoot) Leaf Extract, Valine, Vitis Vinifera (Grape) Seed Extract, Phenoxyethanol, Sodium Benzoate, Sodium Metabisulfite.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: Absolutely Works
reviews.comments: At 65 my lashes have thinned out to almost barely there and 6 months ago was recommended this at an Ulta store.  I have tried other brands with little success.  GrandeLash-MD offers a travel size so bought that to try to save some money and glad I did!  It really works.  Use once every night after taking off make-up and after 3 weeks saw a very noticeable difference and now at 6 months - my lashes look great!  At one time I did consider getting eye lash fillers but so glad I found this to work on my natural lashes.

reviews.headline: Less product than before
reviews.comments: This works, but the last two 6 month supply containers that I purchased ran out within weeks.  I am hoping they were in a bad batch that didn't get filled up all the way, but very expensive for very little product for my most recent purchases.

reviews.headline: This product is fantastic!
reviews.comments: I have visible results in less than 4 weeks. I would purchase again and again.

reviews.headline: Did the Formula Change?
reviews.comments: I've used and loved for years but my most recent purchase hurt. Washed my eyes out for at least a minute after applying before the burn stopped. Thought maybe it was me, bad day, etc so tried again. Same. Returning tomorrow.

reviews.headline: I will continue to buy this product
reviews.comments: It took nearly 8 weeks of application to see results but when I did they were amazing. My lashes are long and lush. I'm a woman of  age and initial thought that I was too old to get results. Happily, I was wrong. Great product.

reviews.headline: WORKS!!
reviews.comments: Honestly, I didn't really know if it would work BUT IT DID! I even put it on my eyebrows. It made them thicker also! I am so impressed I bought the stuff for my hair too! Haven't used it long enough yet but since it worked so well on my eyes, I figured why not try the stuff for your hair?! Very pricey but WORKS!

reviews.headline: ulta üëéüèª
reviews.comments: I've bought this product before in the past from the ulta app and i decided to buy it again because I personally liked it and it came with no product in it what so ever, such a waste of money.

reviews.headline: Works, but expensive
reviews.comments: I'm almost done with my sample size (3 month supply) and ive noticed zero irritation and my lashes are super long and a little bit thicker. My only con is you have to use it every night to keep the results and its verrrry expensive.

reviews.headline: Lash enhancing serum
reviews.comments: This is my go to. I will continue to buy this product.

reviews.headline: Expensive and doesn't work
reviews.comments:
Grande Cosmetics GrandeLASH-MD Lash
Enhancing Serum
I have purchased this item twice (3 tubes each time). First time I used it as intended- once a day‚Ä¶. I saw no difference. A year later I thought ok let me give this a try again maybe I wasn't as dedicated‚Ä¶ I put this stuff on morning and night, TWICE a day!! Over 6 months going into my 7th month and still see NO difference!! No extra length or thickness! Waste of money and product doesn't work‚Ä¶

reviews.headline: WHEN YOU STOP USING IT‚Ä¶
reviews.comments: Yes it works. It works too well. It makes your lases extremly long. HOWEVER COMMA when you stop using it your eyelashes WILL FALL OUT!!! They become dependent on the serum and they turn brittle and thin when you stop using it. It is a vicious and evil cycle to get you to buy more. Way too expensive and not worth losing all of your lashes!!! Use castor oil instead!

reviews.headline: Love this stuff!
reviews.comments: Got them when the mini was on sale and I was hooked!  I had story lashes, mascara did make them look that much better, I figured why not‚Ä¶ after using EVERY day around the 4 week period my lashes were growing üíó I FaceTimed with my daughter AB's she noticed them and a visit to my parents house, mom noticed right away! Both have since purchased after seeing mine.

reviews.headline: It works!
reviews.comments: A friend recommended and this stuff works! I bought the travel size in May and still have plenty. I notice a huge difference! When i wear mascara it looks like I have extensions. Im very pleased with this product!

reviews.headline: IT WORKS AND WORTH THE PRICE
reviews.comments: I bought the travel size one and it actually last you 3 months, REMOVE BLACK TUBE STOPPER FOR MORE PRODUCT. My lashes have grown beautifully and evenly in just 3 months.

reviews.headline: Can't believe they're still selling this crap
reviews.comments:
I used this years ago (over 8 years) and told friends and family not to use it after a bad experience with it. Now im here telling you. 
It can make your dark circles worse if you have any already that you're worried about. Anyone I know that used it has had under eye/top eye lif redness/ itchy eyes. It has Prostaglandin in it (which is known to cause darkening of the skin around the eyes and fat around the eyes being lost. Look it up yourself on google)
For those who it works for thats great and im happy for you but pelase keep an eye out if you start developing a dark lash line. Prostaglandins van cause inflammation.. inflammation causes pigmentation. Before you buy, please understand the possible risks!!! 
From someone that hates fake sponsored products, fake reviewers, those who only try to sell products and not accept the HONEST negative feedback from customers, take this one please!

reviews.headline: Gives false lashes results
reviews.comments: I got this product as a sample size for my free birthday gift, and within a couple of weeks I was noticing length in my lashes. A couple more weeks brought increased thickness. I completely used up my sample and bought the larger size and I'm about 3 months in of using every night and I can't believe how long, thick, and curled my lashes are. I've even had people ask where I get my lashes done, thinking I've got extensions. It's worth every single penny!

reviews.headline: Horrible do not buy!!!
reviews.comments: It is awful. At first I noticed my lashes were getting longer and they were fine for a while. But then I woke up one day my eye was so red, so inflamed and I had a huge stye. It is a huge waste of money. I do not recommend getting this to anyone‚Ä¶

reviews.headline: absolutely works
reviews.comments: I have tried three different serums for my lashes cuz I want to have natural lengthy full lashes without lash extensions and I also were losing lashes and some areas of my eyelid. this is my first bottle and it has lasted me over 2 months now and already see a huge difference. it actually works so well that if you do not want lashes growing into your corners of your eyes in areas that normally do not have lashes do not put the serum there. I was putting this on my eyelids from the very corner all the way to the outside corner and noticed after 4 weeks that I was feeling something in my eye and it was lashes growing in the very corner of my eyelid where you don't normally have lashes growing. this is absolutely the best out there worth the money it is pricey but it does last for a long time and a little goes a long way.

reviews.headline: Works for some but not for everyone
reviews.comments: I got it as a freebie works great for my mom but i have noticed every time i use it i start to get stys in my eyes.

reviews.headline: Amazing!
reviews.comments: I love this serum so much i used to have very very stubby eyelashes but now they are so long! Its very pricey but so worth it!

faceoff_positive.comments:
I originally bought this direct from Grande Cosmetics after receiving a sample of their unique and effective mascara in one of my JustFab boxes. I bought the Yvette set with the growth serum and lash conditioner. THIS WORKS!! I strongly suspect that whoever reviewed that this product didn't actually lengthen their lashes was victim to one or more of the following:
- They didn't apply it right close to their lash line.
- They didn't apply it to clean skin, or they applied it AFTER their eye cream.
- They applied too little product. 
- They are a competitor and aren't being genuine. 
- They didn't use it for at least 4-6 weeks before leaving their review
- Maybe because they didn't use the lash conditioner? I bought the serum with the lash conditioner and always applied the two together
- They rub their eyes too much or use lash damaging eyelash curlers too much, or get their Lactic/glycolic acid facial serum over their lashes when they apply it to the rest of their face (which can be damaging to hair). 
- Fluke bad product? I would definitely contact the company for a replacement as long as it didn't cause you an allergic or bad reaction!

I used one 3-month supply size container, and only used it regularly about 75 percent of the time and before it was empty, my sparse, short eyelashes were at least 1.5-2mm longer than at the start. I wish I were the type to remember to take before and after pics, because my results matched those on the brand's website. 

If you don't seem to be having luck with your product, try going through the list above and tweaking your routine. I really can't imagine it not working for some people due to some flaw in the product, unless your body just won't respond to those kinds of ingredients. It's more likely user error (hey, no offense, we all just want something that works, right? Try to troubleshoot and reap the benefits!)

As for Cons: This product, like every other lash growth serum I have tried, WILL irritate your eyes if you over-apply product and it drips in your eyes. Actually, it WILL irritate your eyes if it's gets in your eye at all. You still need to apply it close to your lash line for it to work, pretty much touching the base of your lashes, and enough as though you were thinly lining your eyes with liner. For me, the almost inevitable irritation was acceptable because that's the nature of that kind of product (even the brands that say they are non-irritating, still irritate my eyeballs). 

Maybe the lash conditioner really helped give me the best results? I haven't tried the serum without it. 

Another Con: The lengthening effects disappear as your lashes naturally fall out. I noticed mine had gone back to normal length after a few months of non-use of the product. I'd say it's a little like Botox‚Ä¶you will have to make an investment every 3-6 months (I'd say every 6 in this case), in order to maintain your results.

faceoff_negative.comments: I got this for Christmas and immediately tried it later that night. First of all, I HATE the applicator, it's such a thin, tiny brush that barely feels like it's coating your lashes. I had to touch it multiple times to see if it was even picking up any product. So I applied it to my upper and lower lash line, as recommended, and as soon as I blinked, it BURNED, BAD! I had to wipe my eyes with micellar water which totally defeats the purpose of applying it in the first place. When I was finally able to blink without my eyes being irritated, my eyes were bloodshot and red--literally the most terrifying and sickly thing I've seen! I tried it again the next night and figured maybe I just had to get used to it but no, SAME THING! Like the burning was unbearable! Every time I blinked it got worse until I eventually couldn't take it and just flushed out my eyes with water. I'm so so disappointed because I really wanted to like this after hearing sm about it online and after begging my mom for it. But it's literally awful and it should NOT sting like this. I asked my mom to return it because I don't see the point in using it if it burns so badly and I literally go blind for 5 minutes before deciding to wash it off anyways. VERY LET DOWN!
faceoff_negative.headline: Burns SO BAD!
